23/08/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- A wildfire continued to rage on the island of Evia on Sunday (August 22nd), fanned by strong winds. Flames destroyed four houses, prompting some tourists to flee their hotels. Authorities say the fire has now changed direction, away from inhabited areas. At least four smaller fires are burning on the south side of the island of Crete. (AP, ANA-MPA - 22/08/10)
